  <span id="freeText6911079976049474030" style="display:none">While reading “Love me while I’m gone” you could pick and emotion out of the dictionary and I’m sure I had felt it. What a rollercoaster of emotions! <br /><br />Emily and Collin are such great characters. Their relationship was so addicting. The second book is all about Emily and Collin’s story (who were Ava’s friends from the first book in the series “My demons best friends) their love story is beautiful and very lovely. This book shows the hardships of a relationship and the things people to need to do to fix it. Not in a boring way though! this book was for sure a page turner. <br /><br />This book felt very real. The dialogue was so relatable and I felt like I could know Emily and Collin as friends. When reading this book I got a lot of that “little pain in my chest” no not a chest infection, A butterfly feeling! <br /><br />If you’re a fan of a good, real, relatable, romance contemporary novel I would highly recommend this one! </span>
