<div id="review_1467498725" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1467498725" />
    <a title="Habiba Hasabo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28244294-habiba-hasabo"><img alt="Habiba Hasabo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1628180788p2/28244294.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1467498725?book_show_action=true">Dec 13, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Habiba Hasabo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Habiba Hasabo" href="/user/show/28244294-habiba-hasabo">Habiba Hasabo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1467498725" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18289205518958083375">*COPY PROVIDED BY AUTHOR FOR AN HONEST REVIEW.* <br/><br/>This book should come with a warning. <br/><br/>WARNING: This book contains too much cuteness and passion. You&apos;ll get addicted, you will swoon, you will want your own Collin, you will want to be a doctor and travel the world! <br/><br/><b>&quot;For now all I want is to find myself.&quot;</b><br/><br/>Emily needs a hug. She is so beautiful, inside out. I felt like she was so simple and pure. This girl had a good sense of humor. <br/>She fell in love quickly, but deeply. She was strong and confident. </span>
  <span id="freeText18289205518958083375" style="display:none">*COPY PROVIDED BY AUTHOR FOR AN HONEST REVIEW.* <br /><br />This book should come with a warning. <br /><br />WARNING: This book contains too much cuteness and passion. You'll get addicted, you will swoon, you will want your own Collin, you will want to be a doctor and travel the world! <br /><br /><b>"For now all I want is to find myself."</b><br /><br />Emily needs a hug. She is so beautiful, inside out. I felt like she was so simple and pure. This girl had a good sense of humor. <br />She fell in love quickly, but deeply. She was strong and confident. She didn't hate making the first move, bold Emily. <br />Yet, you could still find the sensitive and shy Emily lurking inside. <br /><br />Even Collin described her perfectly <b>" In a way, this city is a lot like you. Sensitive, but fierce. Exquisite and fascinating"</b><br /><br />I loved Emily, so much!! I easily connected with her and reading her chapters made me smile. <br /><br /><b>"Can you lose your mind from missing someone too much?"</b><br /><br />Emily made Collin lose his mind. He deserved it. Yup, he was an idiot. I wanted Emily to torture him more!!! But after reading, I believe that it was better when their relationship was postponed, they just had the chance to grow up and apart, experience different things, but was it true love? Well, they managed to find the way back to each other. <br />Collin was sweet and full of life despite his past, I was impressed when he kept on fighting for her. Now, thats a keeper! <br /><br /><b>"But the heart is stupid. A stupid, contracting muscle who doesn't understand how easy it is to get broken all over again. It keeps feeling invincible and some days, it almost convinces me of the fact. Good thing I know better."</b><br /><br />I want to high five the author for an amazing cover and a straight to the point, sweet blurb. <br />This book is really good for Valentine, it gives the whole "love is in the air" vibe. <br /><br /><b>"I miss you everyday. Every city."</b><br /><br />I am happy after finishing this book. I just sighed in happiness. <br />Two incomplete characters who completed each other perfectly, a fun squad that we welcomed again in this book, a story to remember and daydream about later on, what else can I ask for? <br />I also got to know how to write "I miss you" in several languages. Perfect I swear!!! <br /><br /><b>"He's telling me he misses me from every city, in every language. And every time, my heart replies."</b><br /><br />The title of this book was so fitting. Because still after everything, Emily managed to love Collin while he was gone!</span>
  <a data-text-id="18289205518958083375" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


