<div id="review_1868148905" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1868148905" />
    <a title="Kaylin Beach" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41411995-kaylin-beach"><img alt="Kaylin Beach" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483743552p2/41411995.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1868148905?book_show_action=true">Jan 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kaylin Beach" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kaylin Beach" href="/user/show/41411995-kaylin-beach">Kaylin Beach</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/32496527-love-me-while-i-m-gone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1868148905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8292766415719467951">&quot;She could rule the world if she decided that&apos;s what she wanted to do. For now, I&apos;ll just have to pray she doesn&apos;t decide to rule me, because she totally could. And I would let her, without even a fight.&quot;<br/><br/>I adored Love Me While I&apos;m Gone for so many reasons. The main reason being that all the characters from Our Demons, Best Friends were in this book as well! The Half of Me series is absolutely amazing and I love that each book focuses on a different character&apos;s story. Diana T. Scott has created a</span>
  <span id="freeText8292766415719467951" style="display:none">"She could rule the world if she decided that's what she wanted to do. For now, I'll just have to pray she doesn't decide to rule me, because she totally could. And I would let her, without even a fight."<br /><br />I adored Love Me While I'm Gone for so many reasons. The main reason being that all the characters from Our Demons, Best Friends were in this book as well! The Half of Me series is absolutely amazing and I love that each book focuses on a different character's story. Diana T. Scott has created an amazing series with even more amazing characters!<br /><br />Love Me While I'm Gone is book two in the series. Book two is about Collin and Emily! Collin and Emily first met through Emily's sister Lana. Lana just so happens to be working at the same place as Collin. Emily is trying really hard to rekindle her relationship with her sister and in the meantime starts to create a relationship with Collin. Emily and Collin keep there relationship to themselves, and they like it that way. Emily was really started to change Collin. Collin was becoming a better/ happier person because of Emily and their relationship! Unfortunately, this all changes in a matter of hours. Collin just disappears! He leaves one day, without telling Emily anything. Then.. Collin really has the nerve to come back into Emily's life 2 years later? Yup, you read that correctly! Collin is back. Where did he go? Why did he leave? Why didn't he tell Emily? You guys will definitely need to read this book to find out! This book is incredible and I promise you will not regret it! I could easily tell you guys why he left and what happens next, but I really do try my hardest not to spoil the book for anyone.<br /><br />After reading the first book in this series, I did not think any book could beat it! Our Demons, Best Friends was such a great book. I was surprised when I finished this book, because I enjoyed it just as much, if not more! Diana T. Scott's books just keep getting better and better! Her covers are absolutely beautiful too! How could you not love these books?<br /><br />Scott really knows how to create amazing characters! Her characters are so complex and full of history. I felt like I knew each and every one of them. I truly felt connected to them, like they were all my friends and I was dealing with all their problems along with them. That is when you definitely know you are reading a well written book! A reader should always be able to relate to the characters and be able to place themselves into the book!<br /><br />I really liked Collin in the first book, so I was super exited to find out that this book was about him. Collin is super mysterious and quiet, so I really enjoyed getting to see a little bit more of his life and his story! Collin is definitely book boyfriend material and he can email me anytime!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8292766415719467951" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


