<div id="review_1516006124" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1516006124" />
    <a title="Ashley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39480601-ashley"><img alt="Ashley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1422751311p2/39480601.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1516006124?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ashley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ashley" href="/user/show/39480601-ashley">Ashley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1516006124&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1516006124" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7871327933434983137">*Spoilers ahead!*<br/><br/><br/><br/>I just finished Love Me While I&apos;m Gone this afternoon and man did it live up to its expectations! <br/>Although I think I&apos;m either to young or inexperienced in the field because Em was getting on my nerves a little. Don&apos;t get me wrong though I absolutely adore her character, she&apos;s strong yet sensitive, confident but not cocky. She&apos;s pretty sweet but in my opinion she needed to give Collin a chance for explaining himself. Although I do understand how hurt she was, I guess it would be </span>
  <span id="freeText7871327933434983137" style="display:none">*Spoilers ahead!*<br /><br /><br /><br />I just finished Love Me While I'm Gone this afternoon and man did it live up to its expectations! <br />Although I think I'm either to young or inexperienced in the field because Em was getting on my nerves a little. Don't get me wrong though I absolutely adore her character, she's strong yet sensitive, confident but not cocky. She's pretty sweet but in my opinion she needed to give Collin a chance for explaining himself. Although I do understand how hurt she was, I guess it would be hard to let him back in. But then I felt so bad for Collin, having to go through so much pain of losing a good friend, trying to console his best friend by following him overseas only to lose the girl he loves. How tough is that? That's possibly why Em was making me want to lock them in a room together, just so thy could make up because Collin seriously deserved it and they are so good together!<br /><br />I adore the characters continuous sarcastic conversations and wit. It always made me crack a smile. I especially adored Emily in this book more so than in the first one because it showed a lot more of her personality. And her amazing present giving skills, I'm seriously in awe! <br /><br />I was also so pleased with the family's development as a whole, the way that the parents seemed to 'mature' for lack of better word and accept their daughters choices made me so happy. Both of the girls deserved that. <br /><br />In all this book was pleasing in so many ways. It has exceptional sarcasm, amazing friendships, different perspectives and the right amount of an emotional roller coaster to keep you hooked. </span>
