<div id="review_1627771016" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1627771016" />
    <a title="Bea Flores" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42731939-bea-flores"><img alt="Bea Flores" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521301579p2/42731939.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1627771016?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bea Flores" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bea Flores" href="/user/show/42731939-bea-flores">Bea Flores</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1627771016" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9298449371915634597">Love Me While I&apos;m Gone by Diana T. Scott is the second novel in the Half of Me series. It follows Emily &amp; Collin&apos;s journey discovering love. When they first met each other, they knew there was something between them. Young minds, fresh hearts, they took the chance to express each other what they feel. Until an accident happened that Collin needed to leave.<br/><br/>I give this book 4.5 out of 5 stars! It was a great read. I love the characters, they all felt real. The setting was new to me that&apos;s why it t</span>
  <span id="freeText9298449371915634597" style="display:none">Love Me While I'm Gone by Diana T. Scott is the second novel in the Half of Me series. It follows Emily &amp; Collin's journey discovering love. When they first met each other, they knew there was something between them. Young minds, fresh hearts, they took the chance to express each other what they feel. Until an accident happened that Collin needed to leave.<br /><br />I give this book 4.5 out of 5 stars! It was a great read. I love the characters, they all felt real. The setting was new to me that's why it took me days to finish it. The plot's common but as I always say, I find this book unique not because of the plot but because of the way it was handled. Good writing!<br /><br />I gave it 4.5 out of 5 stars because I was searching for something. Don't get me wrong, I like the book and all. I just didn't like it that much enough to say I love it. But it's almost there.<br /><br />There were a few typos I found when reading the book. I don't know if they were typos or not but for me, it is. Anyways, that can be edited. The story's amazing. You should go check it out! That way, you may like it better than I do!<br /><br />I recommend this to people who loves light read stories. Indeed a great read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9298449371915634597" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


