<div id="review_2127874631" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2127874631" />
    <a title="Erin McCoy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/61757374-erin-mccoy"><img alt="Erin McCoy" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2127874631?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erin McCoy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erin McCoy" href="/user/show/61757374-erin-mccoy">Erin McCoy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/28964475-love-me-while-i-m-gone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2127874631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4005362704380539858">Loved this second book in the author’s Half of Me series. The relationship that grows between Collin and Emily is a genuine romance based upon connection, friendship, and love that finally gets to the steam. Collin made a great romantic Hero until he royally screwed it all up. Both of these characters were immensely likable and pulled you into the story. This book runs concurrent with the first of the series and it was great to see the relationship between Sebastian and Ava through others’ eyes.</span>
  <span id="freeText4005362704380539858" style="display:none">Loved this second book in the author’s Half of Me series. The relationship that grows between Collin and Emily is a genuine romance based upon connection, friendship, and love that finally gets to the steam. Collin made a great romantic Hero until he royally screwed it all up. Both of these characters were immensely likable and pulled you into the story. This book runs concurrent with the first of the series and it was great to see the relationship between Sebastian and Ava through others’ eyes. And interesting to see Emily’s machinations behind the scenes helping it along!<br /><br />I read the excerpt at the back for the third book, and am excited to read it. Sounds intriguing, and I’m sure it will be up to the same standard as these previous two.<br /><br />I voluntarily read an advance reader copy in exchange for an honest review.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4005362704380539858" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

