        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1460073322" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12658714990108774414">Firstly I had to go and change the rating for “ Our Demons,Best Friends” because “ Love me while I’m gone “ is beyond perfect!<br/>Don’t get me wrong, I loved the first one too,but this one doesn’t have as much drama as the first one,plus every couple must have their unique love story.<br/>Read this on Christmas morning and I couldn’t have made myself a better present! I knew the author planned a sequel and I was excited for it, but like always real life happened and didn’t have time to read it in one go,</span>
  <span id="freeText12658714990108774414" style="display:none">Firstly I had to go and change the rating for “ Our Demons,Best Friends” because “ Love me while I’m gone “ is beyond perfect!<br>Don’t get me wrong, I loved the first one too,but this one doesn’t have as much drama as the first one,plus every couple must have their unique love story.<br>Read this on Christmas morning and I couldn’t have made myself a better present! I knew the author planned a sequel and I was excited for it, but like always real life happened and didn’t have time to read it in one go, so I postponed it.<br>Overall the book is well-paced, with the right amount of intensity at the right moments just to keep you on your toes! Basically an emotional roller-coaster because it has all kinds of emotions.<br>One thing I love about this author is the way she writes the prologues. It captivates you right from the start,wanting to get to that same point as in the prologue.<br>First part of the book is all about how they fall in love and I swear it’s just perfect, you can see they are soulmates(won’t expand because I don’t want to be a spoiler,read it if you want to know).<br>If you have read the first book,you know tragedy strucks and so their love is on hold.<br>The way the author handles the aftermath is just brilliant, especially the ending.<br>This book is among my favourites books especially because the author improved her writing style and she also wrote from both perspectives,which I absolutely love. I like knowing the guy’s feelings and thoughts.<br>Collin is so dreamy. Smart,hot,sweet, a guy who knows what he wants and goes for it and doesn’t give up. <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1451940845i/17624141._SY540_.jpg" width="300" height="400" alt="Collin" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br>Emily is a strong,funny,smart,beautiful woman! Inside and outside. <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1451940925i/17624157.jpg" width="300" height="400" alt="Emily" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br>If the book would’ve been written only from one POV , I don’t know if I would’ve loved it as much as I do.<br>Can’t wait for the next instalment!<br></span>
  <a data-text-id="12658714990108774414" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


