<div id="review_1453227850" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1453227850" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9294623-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612556938p2/9294623.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1453227850?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/9294623-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1453227850" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5981973452781097212">Lovely romance,relateable characters!<br/><br/><br/>I was really happy to get this book to read as half of me book #1 was one of my favourites that I read last year. <br/><br/>First thing I was so happy to see Colin&apos;s story explored in this book as I was intrigued to his character. From the beginning I was with Emily and Colin on their journey. I loved how the beginning grips you straight away and even if you know the reasons for the characters separation your still totally heartbroken for them and a few points in the s</span>
  <span id="freeText5981973452781097212" style="display:none">Lovely romance,relateable characters!<br /><br /><br />I was really happy to get this book to read as half of me book #1 was one of my favourites that I read last year. <br /><br />First thing I was so happy to see Colin's story explored in this book as I was intrigued to his character. From the beginning I was with Emily and Colin on their journey. I loved how the beginning grips you straight away and even if you know the reasons for the characters separation your still totally heartbroken for them and a few points in the story I wanted to scream COMMUNICATE! I think that just shows how the author makes you totally invest in characters and above everything else that's what keeps me reading.<br /><br />I don't want to spoil anything but if you loved book one, you get to learn more about characters you've read before and also follow a new romance. I really enjoyed this book there were some great moments that made me feel for characters as well as made me smile.<br /><br />As other reviews have said the ending did feel a little rushed as I felt that you were going through this journey with Emily and Colin and when the ending was resolved we didn't get much time to see see them together. I wanted more moments to show them as a couple. Maybe that's the romantic in me though as I am a sucker for a happy ending.<br /><br />Plus, even though I was happy the story concentrated on the romance one thing I missed from book is that struggle that Ava went through in book 1 working at hospital. Even though at points it was mentioned. Emily had just started her first year at the hospital so would have a liked a bit more of hospital life. <br /><br />Overall like I've said this was quick and enjoyable read I felt book 1 had a fuller story. But as I was expecting I love the characters move over Ava and Sebastian welcome Emily and Colin.<br /><br />*sent for honest review*</span>
  <a data-text-id="5981973452781097212" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


