  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1446975465" />
    <a title="Maria Gandolfo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48589800-maria-gandolfo"><img alt="Maria Gandolfo" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1446975465?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria Gandolfo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria Gandolfo" href="/user/show/48589800-maria-gandolfo">Maria Gandolfo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1446975465" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6471503251525360398">I&apos;m not sure to be good at leaving a review. I would give in the simplest way possible my own opinion about this book.<br/>I must admit that, when ive started, i was waiting for a specific line to follow. From the experience of the previous book &quot;Our Demons, Best Friends&quot;, book that left me almost speechless, i was expecting for a dark and really deep book, but with &quot;Love Me While I&apos;m Gone&quot; I found a new meaning for the word &quot;deep&quot;.<br/>If I could judge the two books, one beside the other, id rate them as</span>
  <span id="freeText6471503251525360398" style="display:none">I'm not sure to be good at leaving a review. I would give in the simplest way possible my own opinion about this book.<br />I must admit that, when ive started, i was waiting for a specific line to follow. From the experience of the previous book "Our Demons, Best Friends", book that left me almost speechless, i was expecting for a dark and really deep book, but with "Love Me While I'm Gone" I found a new meaning for the word "deep".<br />If I could judge the two books, one beside the other, id rate them as The night and the Day. Totally different. I think that who is approaching this read after the first one, should not look for a competition but should just enjoy the differences between them. Differences that are dimostrating how Diana is skilled, skilled in facing different situations, with different moods. This made me enjoying the book but not from the first read, because, as said, i was really limited from the scent left from the first one =) After I took a right breath i understood the real value of this piece. <br /><br />The story runs fast, but always keeps you glued with a feet on the past. Would I recommend this book? YES.<br />Would I compare it with the first and judge which is better? I would not. There is no competition, Just take the book itself, enjoy the "crossovering" parts and start to travel in a new emotional Trip.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6471503251525360398" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
