<div id="review_1685387782" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1685387782" />
    <a title="Prarinthepustakaaley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57070594-prarinthepustakaaley"><img alt="Prarinthepustakaaley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1512650493p2/57070594.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1685387782?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Prarinthepustakaaley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Prarinthepustakaaley" href="/user/show/57070594-prarinthepustakaaley">Prarinthepustakaaley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1685387782&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1685387782" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13089505093009210563">** I was fortunate enough to receive this book from the author in exchange for an honest review**<br/><br/><br/>I forgot just how easy it is to read Diana’s books. This was yet another beautiful tale from her. The first book made me swoon, this book made me swoon harder. Diana’s words are magic. I have never fallen in love so easily with a book’s characters. <br/><br/><br/><b>“I can’t tell you how difficult it is to find people with the same sense of humor as mine. It’s such a nice feeling to find company for your weirdly wired</b></span>
  <span id="freeText13089505093009210563" style="display:none">** I was fortunate enough to receive this book from the author in exchange for an honest review**<br /><br /><br />I forgot just how easy it is to read Diana’s books. This was yet another beautiful tale from her. The first book made me swoon, this book made me swoon harder. Diana’s words are magic. I have never fallen in love so easily with a book’s characters. <br /><br /><br /><b>“I can’t tell you how difficult it is to find people with the same sense of humor as mine. It’s such a nice feeling to find company for your weirdly wired brain.” </b><br /><br /><br />This book took me on a rollercoaster of emotions. I felt it all, love, heartbreak, aching, happiness, everything! I feel so satisfied with the fact that Diana decided to start and end the book before and after Ava and Sebastian’s story, that way I knew what was happening in both of the stories.<br /><br />Emily and Collin were young and in love, and that was the most beautiful of them all. I never knew that people could fall in love at a hospital. I was so into the book that I wanted to smack Collin’s head when he left Em, I had to resist the urge to kiss Collin everyday but ugh “fictional characters” I really loved this book and the story, however, Ava and Sebastian’s story will be my favorite. A must must must read for everyone who has a beating heart. Read this series and fall in love!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13089505093009210563" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


